President Trump addressed the American Farm Bureau Federation's annual convention in Austin, Texas, where he highlighted his administration's achievements in supporting American farmers and ranchers. He mentioned the successful renegotiation of the North American Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA), now known as the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA), as well as the groundbreaking trade deal with China. Trump also emphasized his commitment to protecting American agriculture, cutting regulations, and promoting energy independence. He announced the withdrawal of a proposed rule by the Army Corps of Engineers that would have given the federal government greater control over farmers' access to water. Additionally, he discussed his administration's efforts to improve rural broadband access and support rural communities.